When she woke up
less than a minute later,

161
00:06:38,667 --> 00:06:41,234
she was 50 years older.

162
00:06:41,234 --> 00:06:43,501
I can guarantee you...

163
00:06:43,501 --> 00:06:46,367
this is a first.

164
00:06:48,100 --> 00:06:49,200
Excuse me.

165
00:06:53,701 --> 00:06:54,934
Are you okay, dr. Burkhoff?

166
00:06:54,934 --> 00:06:56,934
Fine.
Not enough sleep, that's all.

167
00:06:56,934 --> 00:06:58,501
Research.

168
00:06:58,501 --> 00:07:00,133
Well, what do we do now?

169
00:07:00,133 --> 00:07:01,567
Is there any way
to reverse this?

170
00:07:02,901 --> 00:07:04,267
I wish i knew.

171
00:07:04,267 --> 00:07:05,434
I need...

172
00:07:05,434 --> 00:07:07,534
to do some thinking.

173
00:07:16,934 --> 00:07:18,701
Are you my mother?

174
00:07:29,100 --> 00:07:31,934
Isabelle?

175
00:07:49,434 --> 00:07:51,801
Every day,
the 4400 are changing

176
00:07:51,801 --> 00:07:53,133
and getting stronger.

177
00:07:53,133 --> 00:07:55,968
Instead of mobilizing
to meet this challenge,

178
00:07:55,968 --> 00:07:57,334
we're wringing our hands

179
