conspiracy

237
00:10:07,234 --> 00:10:09,968
without some
cabinet-level approval?

238
00:10:09,968 --> 00:10:10,968
That's correct.

239
00:10:10,968 --> 00:10:12,300
I was given
a broad mandate

240
00:10:12,300 --> 00:10:13,834
in my duties

241
00:10:13,834 --> 00:10:15,300
as head of ntac.

242
00:10:15,300 --> 00:10:17,801
I felt that the project fell
within that mandate,

243
00:10:17,801 --> 00:10:20,000
so there was no need
to seek outside approval.

244
00:10:24,834 --> 00:10:26,300
Excuse us, everybody.

245
00:10:26,300 --> 00:10:27,534
Did you hear that?

246
00:10:27,534 --> 00:10:29,267
Well, yeah, the microphones
went haywire.

247
00:10:29,267 --> 00:10:31,667
No, no, not that.
Something else.

248
00:10:31,667 --> 00:10:33,267
Just set that
approval issue

249
00:10:33,267 --> 00:10:35,033
to the side
for the moment.

250
00:10:36,901 --> 00:10:38,534
Did you ever
discuss the project

251
00:10:38,534 --> 00:10:40,267
with anyone outside of ntac?

252
00:10:40,267 --> 00:10:42,267
I mean, someone
somewhere

253
00:10:42,267 --> 00:10:43,734
must have taken an interest

254
00:10:43,734 --> 00:10:45,133
in what you people
were doing over there.

255
00:10:45,133 --> 00:10:46,701
[Whispering]

256
00:10:46,701 --> 00:10:48,000
It's a simple question,
mr. Ryland.

257
00:10:49,667 --> 00:10:54,300
Surely it can't be
that difficult to answer.

258
00:10:54,300 --> 00:11:03,734
If i could have your attention
up here, mr. Ryland...

259
00:11:03,734 --> 00:11:05,167
[gasping]

260
00:11:07,868 --> 00:11:10,100
Security!
Stop that man!

261
00:11:16,834 --> 00:11:17,868
