an ambulance!

264
00:11:20,901 --> 00:11:23,133
Stand back, please!
Back! Get back!

265
00:11:28,667 --> 00:11:29,601
Hey!

266
00:11:45,367 --> 00:11:47,167
Stop! T.j.!

267
00:11:57,701 --> 00:12:00,100
Someone get these photographers
out of here.

268
00:12:00,100 --> 00:12:01,934
Stay over there.

269
00:12:01,934 --> 00:12:03,934
I don't understand what i did.

270
00:12:03,934 --> 00:12:07,534
Would somebody please
tell to me what i just did?

271
00:12:09,501 --> 00:12:10,868
Hang on, dennis.

272
00:12:10,868 --> 00:12:12,801
The ambulance
is coming.

273
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:22,667
Yeah, it was her.

274
00:12:22,667 --> 00:12:23,801
The blood we picked up
at the scene

275
00:12:23,801 --> 00:12:25,267
matches the dna
in our records.

276
00:12:25,267 --> 00:12:27,200
That was t.j. Kim
running from the courthouse.

277
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:28,467
When she hit this place,

278
00:12:28,467 --> 00:12:29,567
t.j. Drove
every man in the building

279
00:12:29,567 --> 00:12:30,934
into a homicidal rage.

280
00:12:30,934 --> 00:12:33,467
Now it sounds
like she just zapped one guy.

281
00:12:33,467 --> 00:12:35,367
She's learning
to control what she can do.

282
00:12:35,367 --> 00:12:36,701
They all are.

283
00:12:36,701 --> 00:12:39,100
Ever since we took them
off the inhibitor,

284
00:12:39,100 --> 00:12:40,467
they're either
developing abilities

285
00:12:40,467 --> 00:12:41,834
or they're refining
the ones that they've got.

286
00:12:41,834 --> 00:12:43,534
So they are getting
more dangerous.

287
00:12:43,534 --> 00:12:45,167
I guess ryland
was right.

288
00:12:45,167 --> 00:12:46,934
I'll be sure to mention that
to my daughter.

289
00:12:46,934 --> 00:12:48,300
Save the point-
counterpoint.

290
00:12:48,300 --> 00:12:49,634
At the moment,

291
00:12:49,634 --> 00:12:50,834
we've been tasked
with two jobs...

292
00:12:50,834 --> 00:12:51,934
we track down t.j. Kim.

293
00:12:51,934 --> 00:12:53,400
What's the second job?

294
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:55,934
We are to protect
ryland's co-conspirators

295
00:12:55,934 --> 00:12:57,601
from any
further reprisals.

296
00:12:57,601 --> 00:12:59,934
So we arrest them,
and now we're their bodyguards?

297
00:12:59,934 --> 00:13:02,133
The entire country just saw
a 4400 turn a government hearing

298
00:13:02,133 --> 00:13:04,367
into her own personal
slasher film.

299
00:13:04,367 --> 00:13:05,667
If t.j.
Gets to ryland again...

300
00:13:05,667 --> 00:13:06,868
or any of them...

301
00:13:06,868 --> 00:13:08,100
before we can
bring her in,

302
00:13:08,100 --> 00:13:09,367
people are going to
start to wonder

303
00:13:09,367 --> 00:13:10,601
if the united states government

304
00:13:10,601 --> 00:13:12,300
is capable
of protecting its citizens,

305
00:13:12,300 --> 00:13:14,834
and that's the beginning
of chaos.

306
00:13:14,834 --> 00:13:16,934
Back to work, please.

307
00:13:26,234 --> 00:13:28,567
Tom...

308
00:13:28,567 --> 00:13:30,467
in case you're wondering,

309
00:13:30,467 --> 00:13:32,601
dennis is still
in surgery.

310
00:13:32,601 --> 00:13:36,133
They say that it is
touch and go.

311
00:14:03,834 --> 00:14:04,834
[Shawn]: It's okay.

312
00:14:04,834 --> 00:14:05,834
Give me your hands.

313
00:14:05,834 --> 00:14:06,868
Try and relax.

314
00:14:06,868 --> 00:14:08,267
Relax.

315
00:14:28,234 --> 00:14:30,000
Is it better?

316
00:14:32,133 --> 00:14:35,200
Much better.

317
00:14:37,133 --> 00:14:38,567
For now.

318
00:14:44,067 --> 00:14:45,367
When this thing first came on,

319
00:14:45,367 --> 00:14:47,300
it was bad,
but at least she was healthy.

320
00:14:47,300 --> 00:14:49,634
Now she's had diabetes,
emphysema...

321
00:14:49,634 --> 00:14:51,100
it seems like every day
there's something new.

322
00:14:51,100 --> 00:14:52,801
I'll come help her every day.

323
00:14:52,801 --> 00:14:54,000
Listen,

324
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:55,400
we've got everyone
working on this.

325
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:56,434
We're going to
figure it out.

326
00:14:56,434 --> 00:14:57,400
Is my mother okay?

327
00:14:57,400 --> 00:14:58,767
Uh, yeah.

328
00:14:58,767 --> 00:15:00,567
She had a little problem.

329
00:15:00,567 --> 00:15:02,300
Shawn fixed it.

330
00:15:02,300 --> 00:15:04,968
It's all
in the wrists.

331
00:15:04,968 --> 00:15:06,567
Can i see her?

332
00:15:09,534 --> 00:15:11,834
Please?

333
00:15:20,100 --> 00:15:22,167
Mom?

334
00:15:25,667 --> 00:15:28,200
[Weakly]: Isabelle.

335
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:29,501
Come here.

336
00:15:29,501 --> 00:15:31,801
Is there anything i can do?

337
00:15:31,801 --> 00:15:33,534
No, i'm... i'm fine.

338
00:15:33,534 --> 00:15:35,467
Really.

339
00:15:35,467 --> 00:15:36,834
Sit down.

340
00:15:40,901 --> 00:15:43,901
You were such a beautiful baby.

341
00:15:43,901 --> 00:15:45,734
I used to hold you

342
00:15:45,734 --> 00:15:47,367
all day long.

343
00:15:47,367 --> 00:15:49,334
I knew exactly
what you were feeling.

344
00:15:49,334 --> 00:15:50,934
What you wanted.

345
00:15:50,934 --> 00:15:52,934
We were so close.

346
00:15:52,934 --> 00:15:54,868
I'm sorry for
growing up so fast.

347
00:15:54,868 --> 00:15:56,601
I didn't mean to.

348
00:15:56,601 --> 00:15:58,667
I didn't want to.

349
00:15:58,667 --> 00:16:01,000
Neither did i.

350
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:08,234
The crazy thing is

351
00:16:08,234 --> 00:16:09,501
i keep thinking
about patty.

352
00:16:09,501 --> 00:16:10,801
Ryland's wife.

353
00:16:10,801 --> 00:16:12,167
I feel like i should
call her or something,

354
00:16:12,167 --> 00:16:13,334
help her through this.

355
00:16:13,334 --> 00:16:14,501
Maybe you should.

356
00:16:14,501 --> 00:16:15,667
You and ryland
were friends

357
00:16:15,667 --> 00:16:16,801
for a long time.

358
00:16:16,801 --> 00:16:18,834
It's okay to be conflicted.

359
00:16:18,834 --> 00:16:21,133
Well, ryland's little experiment
almost got you killed.

360
00:16:21,133 --> 00:16:22,167
Shawn, too.

361
00:16:22,167 --> 00:16:24,033
The guy knew

362
00:16:24,033 --> 00:16:25,200
that kyle was stalking
jordan collier

363
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:26,200
and he did nothing.

364
00:16:26,200 --> 00:16:27,200
I'd say that trumps friendship.

365
00:16:28,667 --> 00:16:30,501
You have so much
on your mind.

366
00:16:30,501 --> 00:16:33,701
Kyle, ryland, the 4400s...

367
00:16:33,701 --> 00:16:35,801
i need to get you
away from here.

368
00:16:35,801 --> 00:16:37,567
Away from your problems.

369
00:16:37,567 --> 00:16:39,200
Yeah, well, that sounds nice,

370
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:40,701
but i can't go anywhere.

371
00:16:40,701 --> 00:16:41,968
I'm starting an investigation

372
00:16:41,968 --> 00:16:43,334
in the morning.

373
00:16:43,334 --> 00:16:44,968
What if i told you

374
00:16:44,968 --> 00:16:46,000
i could take you away

375
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:48,467
between now and then?

376
00:16:48,467 --> 00:16:51,367
My ability.

377
00:16:51,367 --> 00:16:55,767
Since i'm off the inhibitor...

378
00:16:55,767 --> 00:16:57,834
i think i can control it now.

379
00:16:57,834 --> 00:16:59,801
What, you mean you want to...

380
00:16:59,801 --> 00:17:01,801
you want to take me
into another dream world?

381
00:17:01,801 --> 00:17:03,100
Alternate reality...

382
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:04,234
i don't even know
what to call it.

383
00:17:04,234 --> 00:17:05,501
Call it a vacation.

384
00:17:05,501 --> 00:17:07,901
A week, a year...

385
00:17:07,901 --> 00:17:11,200
as long as we want.

386
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:13,701
All that in the space
of a few moments.

387
00:17:15,334 --> 00:17:17,801
Should we try it?

388
00:17:17,801 --> 00:17:19,334
Right here?

389
00:17:19,334 --> 00:17:20,868
Now?

390
00:17:20,868 --> 00:17:22,100
Well, what...

391
00:17:22,100 --> 00:17:23,667
what do we do?

392
00:17:23,667 --> 00:17:26,267
We're already doing it.

393
00:17:37,133 --> 00:17:39,000
There's no one
on the beach.

394
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:40,834
It's all ours, thomas.

395
00:17:40,834 --> 00:17:42,434
So's the hotel.

396
00:17:42,434 --> 00:17:44,834
And we can stay here
for as long as we like.

397
00:17:44,834 --> 00:17:47,567
There is no jet lag.

398
00:17:47,567 --> 00:17:49,367
That sounds perfect.

399
00:17:49,367 --> 00:17:51,133
It feels perfect, too.

400
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:16,434
The door's open. Come in.

401
00:18:18,234 --> 00:18:19,634
Whoa.

402
00:18:19,634 --> 00:18:20,901
What? What is it?

403
00:18:23,400 --> 00:18:25,167
Uh, you're naked.

404
00:18:25,167 --> 00:18:26,501
I'm more comfortable
this way.

405
00:18:26,501 --> 00:18:28,100
I haven't really
gotten used to them.

406
00:18:28,100 --> 00:18:29,300
Clothes.

407
00:18:29,300 --> 00:18:31,367
I have a bathrobe.

408
00:18:36,734 --> 00:18:39,901
Is this better?

409
00:18:39,901 --> 00:18:42,901
Almost.

410
00:19:01,200 --> 00:19:03,133
I never met anybody

411
00:19:03,133 --> 00:19:05,534
that read the encyclopedia
from cover to cover before.

412
00:19:05,534 --> 00:19:06,667
Oh, i'm not finished.

413
00:19:06,667 --> 00:19:08,400
We just delivered those to you
yesterday.

414
00:19:09,801 --> 00:19:11,801
Okay, you're a fast reader.

415
00:19:11,801 --> 00:19:13,200
That's really cool.

416
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:15,334
Um, listen,

417
00:19:15,334 --> 00:19:16,501
they're looking for you
down in the labs.

418
00:19:16,501 --> 00:19:17,534
You're like an hour late.

419
00:19:17,534 --> 00:19:19,501
They sent you to get me?

420
00:19:21,167 --> 00:19:23,033
Aren't you in charge?

421
00:19:23,033 --> 00:19:24,567
Well, yeah,
more or less.

422
00:19:24,567 --> 00:19:26,200
You know,
i go where i'm needed.

423
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:28,300
They were scared of me,
weren't they?

424
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:29,234
Pretty much.

425
00:19:29,234 --> 00:19:30,400
That's all right.

426
00:19:30,400 --> 00:19:32,200
I think even my parents
are frightened of me.

427
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:34,567
I don't think your mom and dad
are scared of you.

428
00:19:34,567 --> 00:19:35,834
I think they're just confused.

429
00:19:35,834 --> 00:19:36,934
I don't blame them.

430
00:19:36,934 --> 00:19:38,334
It's mostly how i feel, too.

431
00:19:38,334 --> 00:19:39,734
I...

432
00:19:39,734 --> 00:19:41,734
don't understand
what happened to me.

433
00:19:41,734 --> 00:19:43,868
I don't understand what happened
to my mother.

434
00:19:43,868 --> 00:19:47,400
And i'm trying to read
and learn things, but...

435
00:19:47,400 --> 00:19:49,501
mostly, i just...

436
00:19:49,501 --> 00:19:52,033
i still feel lost.

437
00:19:52,033 --> 00:19:55,267
See, now you sound
like a real 4400.

438
00:19:55,267 --> 00:19:58,501
But i'm not a 4400...

439
00:19:58,501 --> 00:20:03,033
not like my mother
and father...

440
00:20:03,033 --> 00:20:05,067
or you.

441
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:11,334
Looks like i'm going to live.

442
00:20:11,334 --> 00:20:14,400
Sorry to disappoint you, tom.

443
00:20:16,634 --> 00:20:18,267
Why'd you ask me to see me,
dennis?

444
00:20:18,267 --> 00:20:20,300
I hear
that you and skouris

445
00:20:20,300 --> 00:20:23,167
are in charge
of the investigation.

446
00:20:23,167 --> 00:20:24,300
Yeah, we know who did it.

447
00:20:24,300 --> 00:20:25,567
We'll find her.

448
00:20:25,567 --> 00:20:29,067
T.j. Kim attacked thuildx weeks ago.

449
00:20:29,067 --> 00:20:31,934
No one's
tracked her down yet.

450
00:20:31,934 --> 00:20:34,634
We got a little sidetracked
cleaning up your mess, dennis.

451
00:20:34,634 --> 00:20:36,868
Did you ever think
that maybe she has help?

452
00:20:36,868 --> 00:20:39,667
Other 4400s

453
00:20:39,667 --> 00:20:42,734
who feel the same way
about the government

454
00:20:42,734 --> 00:20:43,701
she does?

455
00:20:43,701 --> 00:20:45,133
When we catch her,
we'll ask.

456
00:20:45,133 --> 00:20:47,567
Will you?

457
00:20:48,968 --> 00:20:50,200
I want to make sure

458
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:51,968
you're going to
take this thing

459
00:20:51,968 --> 00:20:53,901
as far as it goes, tom,

460
00:20:53,901 --> 00:20:56,934
the same way you did
when you came after me...

461
00:20:58,901 --> 00:21:02,534
and i want my people
protected.

462
00:21:02,534 --> 00:21:04,701
They were acting
under my orders.

463
00:21:04,701 --> 00:21:06,200
They're under guard.

464
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:08,734
So was the courthouse
when kim attacked.

465
00:21:08,734 --> 00:21:14,234
I'd feel better
if you brought them in.

466
00:21:14,234 --> 00:21:17,601
We offered sanctuary
to every single conspirator.

467
00:21:17,601 --> 00:21:19,801
There were no takers.

468
00:21:19,801 --> 00:21:22,234
<i>I guess no one</i>
<i>wanted to cooperate</i>

469
00:21:22,234 --> 00:21:23,534
<i>with the organization</i>

470
00:21:23,534 --> 00:21:25,133
<i>that was working</i>
<i>to put you in prison.</i>

471
00:21:25,133 --> 00:21:26,434
<i>We had to fight</i>

472
00:21:26,434 --> 00:21:28,000
<i>just to get them</i>
<i>to let us post agents</i>

473
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:29,200
<i>outside their houses.</i>

474
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:30,267
Crockett!

475
00:21:30,267 --> 00:21:32,734
You ready
to go for a walk, boy?

476
00:21:33,868 --> 00:21:35,133
Come on, crockett.
Let's go.

477
00:21:35,133 --> 00:21:36,734
They wanted no part of us.

478
00:21:36,734 --> 00:21:38,000
They all seemed confident

479
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:39,767
that t.j. Kim
was acting alone.

480
00:21:45,367 --> 00:21:46,501
Crockett?

481
00:21:46,501 --> 00:21:48,868
What's wrong?
It's me.

482
00:22:21,004 --> 00:22:23,803
[Jarvis]: This arrived
15 minutes ago.

483
00:22:25,304 --> 00:22:26,870
[Distorted voice]:
<i>This is a message</i>

484
00:22:26,870 --> 00:22:28,471
<i>from the nova group.</i>

485
00:22:28,471 --> 00:22:30,937
<i>We are the defensive wing</i>
<i>of the 4400.</i>

486
00:22:30,937 --> 00:22:32,371
<i>Today, the world has seen</i>

487
00:22:32,371 --> 00:22:34,638
<i>what happens to those</i>
<i>who try to harm us.</i>

488
00:22:34,638 --> 00:22:37,870
<i>A second demonstration</i>
<i>of our capabilities</i>

489
00:22:37,870 --> 00:22:39,471
<i>is planned for october 19th.</i>

490
00:22:39,471 --> 00:22:40,970
<i>A new era dawns.</i>

491
00:22:40,970 --> 00:22:42,571
Defensive wing, huh?

492
00:22:42,571 --> 00:22:44,437
What happens when they
decide to play offense?

493
00:22:44,437 --> 00:22:45,870
I guess we find out
in five days.

494
00:22:45,870 --> 00:22:47,237
They didn't even say
what they want.

495
00:22:47,237 --> 00:22:48,737
No demands,
no room for compromise.

496
00:22:48,737 --> 00:22:50,037
We don't even know

497
00:22:50,037 --> 00:22:52,204
how many 4400s
are in this nova group.

498
00:22:52,204 --> 00:22:53,504
We couldn't even handle one

499
00:22:53,504 --> 00:22:54,638
when she walked in
and attacked the place.

500
00:22:54,638 --> 00:22:56,404
Now there's a whole team
of assassins out there,

501
00:22:56,404 --> 00:22:58,104
all with abilities?

502
00:22:58,104 --> 00:22:59,404
They've got someone
who can kill you

503
00:22:59,404 --> 00:23:00,604
by lowering your
body temperature.

504
00:23:00,604 --> 00:23:01,737
Don't forget
the beastmaster.

505
00:23:01,737 --> 00:23:02,870
What?

506
00:23:02,870 --> 00:23:04,171
That dog got pissed off
pretty quick.

507
00:23:04,171 --> 00:23:05,271
Well, i've been
all over the files,

508
00:23:05,271 --> 00:23:07,137
and none of these abilities

509
00:23:07,137 --> 00:23:08,504
have been registered
with us.

510
00:23:08,504 --> 00:23:09,703
They're off
the inhibitor now.

511
00:23:09,703 --> 00:23:10,604
We can't even pretend

512
00:23:10,604 --> 00:23:11,670
to have
a comprehensive list

513
00:23:11,670 --> 00:23:13,037
of what these people
can do.

514
00:23:13,037 --> 00:23:14,404
Is anyone feeling...

515
00:23:14,404 --> 00:23:16,803
a little overmatched here?

516
00:23:25,437 --> 00:23:27,237
You two remember gary navarro?

517
00:23:27,237 --> 00:23:29,471
Hey, gary.

518
00:23:29,471 --> 00:23:31,237
Been a while.

519
00:23:31,237 --> 00:23:33,970
You're right, baldwin.

520
00:23:33,970 --> 00:23:35,703
I do think you two sold me out.

521
00:23:35,703 --> 00:23:38,237
It really bothered me
for a while,

522
00:23:38,237 --> 00:23:40,371
but now i understand it's just
standard operating procedure.

523
00:23:40,371 --> 00:23:41,404
Well, i guess

524
00:23:41,404 --> 00:23:42,204
that mind reading thing

525
00:23:42,204 --> 00:23:43,304
is working
pretty well, huh?

526
00:23:43,304 --> 00:23:45,137
Better than ever, actually.

527
00:23:45,137 --> 00:23:46,571
Gary's telepathic abilities
have been very useful

528
00:23:46,571 --> 00:23:48,104
to the national security agency.

529
00:23:48,104 --> 00:23:49,770
They have agreed
to let us borrow him

530
00:23:49,770 --> 00:23:51,404
while we investigate
the nova group.

531
00:23:51,404 --> 00:23:52,770
So you're clear
