00:35:06,104 --> 00:35:07,371
No...

803
00:35:07,371 --> 00:35:08,337
that's what you were thinking,
wasn't it?

804
00:35:08,337 --> 00:35:09,870
Shh.

805
00:35:09,870 --> 00:35:11,037
No, it wasn't.

806
00:35:11,037 --> 00:35:12,537
I don't want her
to die either,

807
00:35:12,537 --> 00:35:13,770
so i'll let you do it.

808
00:35:13,770 --> 00:35:15,571
I'll...
i'll even shut my eyes.

809
00:35:15,571 --> 00:35:17,671
Isabelle...

810
00:35:17,671 --> 00:35:20,404
i would never hurt you.

811
00:35:20,404 --> 00:35:23,037
Why?

812
00:35:23,037 --> 00:35:24,604
I don't understand.

813
00:35:24,604 --> 00:35:25,704
It's the only way to save her.

814
00:35:25,704 --> 00:35:26,770
We don't know that,

815
00:35:26,770 --> 00:35:27,837
and i won't make a choice

816
00:35:27,837 --> 00:35:29,137
between the two of you.

817
00:35:29,137 --> 00:35:31,170
"Won't" or "can't"?

818
00:35:44,803 --> 00:35:46,271
Sorry.

819
00:35:46,271 --> 00:35:48,237
I don't mean
to invade anyone's space.

820
00:35:48,237 --> 00:35:49,604
Oh, that's okay.

821
00:35:49,604 --> 00:35:51,337
It's not my desk.

822
00:35:51,337 --> 00:35:54,937
But it looks like you'll be here
for a while now, huh?

823
00:35:54,937 --> 00:35:56,571
Assuming
this place is still standing

824
00:35:56,571 --> 00:35:57,803
on october 20th,
yeah.

825
00:35:57,803 --> 00:35:59,137
Maybe we should talk
to jarvis.

826
00:35:59,137 --> 00:36:01,638
Get you a room
of your very own.

827
00:36:01,638 --> 00:36:02,870
That's fine with me.

828
00:36:04,404 --> 00:36:05,571
To tell you the truth,

829
00:36:05,571 --> 00:36:07,271
i could use
a little bit of a buffer zone.

830
00:36:09,237 --> 00:36:11,304
This problem you're having
with your daughter's...

831
00:36:11,304 --> 00:36:14,070
precog ability?

832
00:36:14,070 --> 00:36:17,437
I keep wanting
to give you my opinion,

833
00:36:17,437 --> 00:36:19,371
but i don't want to intrude.

834
00:36:19,371 --> 00:36:21,070
So you are...

835
00:36:21,070 --> 00:36:23,070
listening to my thoughts.

836
00:36:23,070 --> 00:36:24,937
You and baldwin.

837
00:36:24,937 --> 00:36:26,170
I can't help it.

838
00:36:26,170 --> 00:36:28,137
I try to tune you guys out,

839
00:36:28,137 --> 00:36:30,837
but every now and then,
something leaks through.

840
00:36:30,837 --> 00:36:33,970
I'll try to keep that in mind.

841
00:36:36,770 --> 00:36:39,404
You said you had an opinion
about maia.

842
00:36:39,404 --> 00:36:40,671
What is it?

843
00:36:40,671 --> 00:36:42,504
When i first...

844
00:36:42,504 --> 00:36:45,404
developed this thing of mine,

845
00:36:45,404 --> 00:36:47,271
i was a basket case.

846
00:36:47,271 --> 00:36:48,437
You saw me.

847
00:36:48,437 --> 00:36:50,638
I truly thought
i was going insane,

848
00:36:50,638 --> 00:36:53,604
so i fought against it,

849
00:36:53,604 --> 00:36:55,770
and that just
made it worse.

850
00:36:55,770 --> 00:36:57,404
I had to give in to it,

851
00:36:57,404 --> 00:36:59,337
let it
take control of me,

852
00:36:59,337 --> 00:37:01,104
and then, slowly,

853
00:37:01,104 --> 00:37:04,537
i learned
how to take control of it.

854
00:37:04,537 --> 00:37:06,137
Listen, your kid
stops fighting,

855
00:37:06,137 --> 00:37:07,471
and eventually,

856
00:37:07,471 --> 00:37:09,903
it'll become
like seeing or hearing

857
00:37:09,903 --> 00:37:11,537
or any other sense.

858
00:37:11,537 --> 00:37:13,704
She won't even
think about it.

859
00:37:13,704 --> 00:37:17,170
It's just a part
of who she is.

860
00:37:20,803 --> 00:37:23,004
That's how it worked
for me, anyway.

861
00:37:26,638 --> 00:37:28,337
Thank you.

862
00:37:28,337 --> 00:37:29,704
Diana.

863
00:37:29,704 --> 00:37:30,970
We just got a call
from the seattle police.

864
00:37:30,970 --> 00:37:31,870
Someone down there
read our apb.

865
00:37:31,870 --> 00:37:33,704
They know exactly
where hauser is.

866
00:37:38,137 --> 00:37:39,304
You guys are lucky,
actually.

867
00:37:39,304 --> 00:37:40,738
In another day or two,

868
00:37:40,738 --> 00:37:42,504
we would have buried him
in potter's field.

869
00:37:42,504 --> 00:37:44,104
Buried who?

870
00:37:44,104 --> 00:37:45,471
Him.

871
00:37:45,471 --> 00:37:47,037
I always read the apb memos

872
00:37:47,037 --> 00:37:48,537
when they circulate
in the police department.

873
00:37:48,537 --> 00:37:51,037
Kind of a hobby.

874
00:37:51,037 --> 00:37:52,738
Gets boring in here.

875
00:37:52,738 --> 00:37:54,471
Anyway, there was
a description

876
00:37:54,471 --> 00:37:55,704
of a regimental tattoo

877
00:37:55,704 --> 00:37:56,803
on the memo for hauser.

878
00:37:56,803 --> 00:37:59,037
82nd airborne.
"Death from above."

879
00:37:59,037 --> 00:38:00,537
I remember it from a john doe

880
00:38:00,537 --> 00:38:02,204
they brought in here
three weeks ago.

881
00:38:02,204 --> 00:38:04,738
This guy drowned
in the harbor.

882
00:38:04,738 --> 00:38:06,604
A lot of veterans
have that tattoo.

883
00:38:06,604 --> 00:38:08,070
Do a lot of veterans

884
00:38:08,070 --> 00:38:09,937
look exactly like
the mug shot you circulated?

885
00:38:09,937 --> 00:38:11,870
Don't believe me?

886
00:38:11,870 --> 00:38:13,471
Take a look
for yourselves.

887
00:38:16,337 --> 00:38:19,004
Say hello
to wesley hauser.

888
00:38:19,508 --> 00:38:20,840
Hauser died

889
00:38:20,840 --> 00:38:22,408
two and a half weeks
before ryland was attacked.

890
00:38:22,408 --> 00:38:24,141
Obviously, that wasn't him
on the phone the other day.

891
00:38:24,141 --> 00:38:26,341
And that copy
of the 4400 report

892
00:38:26,341 --> 00:38:27,774
with all his notes over it?

893
00:38:27,774 --> 00:38:29,007
For all we know,

894
00:38:29,007 --> 00:38:30,707
that could have been a plant.

895
00:38:30,707 --> 00:38:32,508
Somebody wanted us distracted.

896
00:38:32,508 --> 00:38:34,274
They deliberately
put us on the trail

897
00:38:34,274 --> 00:38:36,007
of some phantom member
of the nova group.

898
00:38:36,007 --> 00:38:37,740
I mean, how did we first
find out about hauser?

899
00:38:37,740 --> 00:38:39,840
T.j.'s old boyfriend.
He gave us the address.

900
00:38:39,840 --> 00:38:41,573
No, he was thinking it.

901
00:38:43,540 --> 00:38:44,907
At least,
according to gary, he was.

902
00:38:44,907 --> 00:38:47,508
Gary navarro
put us onto wesley hauser.

903
00:39:07,673 --> 00:39:10,840
Get in.

904
00:39:17,207 --> 00:39:18,807
You lied to me, daniel.

905
00:39:18,807 --> 00:39:21,907
You never said anything
about killing people.

906
00:39:21,907 --> 00:39:23,673
We were protecting you, shawn.

907
00:39:23,673 --> 00:39:26,374
If we tell you in advance,
you're culpable.

908
00:39:26,374 --> 00:39:27,640
[Woman groaning]

909
00:39:32,241 --> 00:39:34,041
What is she doing here?

910
00:39:34,041 --> 00:39:35,640
She's dying.
She needs your help.

911
00:39:35,640 --> 00:39:36,774
I told you,
i don't want

912
00:39:36,774 --> 00:39:38,707
anything more
to do with you.

913
00:39:38,707 --> 00:39:40,540
The nova group
was supposed to protect us.

914
00:39:40,540 --> 00:39:42,207
That's why i gave you money,
daniel.

915
00:39:42,207 --> 00:39:43,640
That's why i gave you money.

916
00:39:43,640 --> 00:39:46,074
Not to start
a terrorist organization!

917
00:39:46,074 --> 00:39:47,107
We'll talk about your concerns
later.

918
00:39:47,107 --> 00:39:48,408
She's got a stomach wound,

919
00:39:48,408 --> 00:39:49,074
and it's infected.

920
00:39:49,074 --> 00:39:50,307
She needs you right now,

921
00:39:50,307 --> 00:39:51,907
or she's not
going to make it.

922
00:39:51,907 --> 00:39:54,341
Shawn, she's a 4400.

923
00:39:54,341 --> 00:39:56,107
If we don't
help each other,

924
00:39:56,107 --> 00:39:58,141
what hope do we have?

925
00:40:01,940 --> 00:40:04,207
Give me your hand.

926
00:41:31,573 --> 00:41:32,874
What are you doing here?

927
00:41:32,874 --> 00:41:35,041
You're awake.

928
00:41:35,041 --> 00:41:36,840
Good.

929
00:41:38,740 --> 00:41:41,174
It's important
that you know it was me.

930
00:41:45,307 --> 00:41:48,474
I'm the guy who killed you.

931
00:41:59,274 --> 00:42:02,807
[Monitor beeping]

932
00:42:11,807 --> 00:42:13,207
[Man on radio]: <i>med post.</i>

933
00:42:13,207 --> 00:42:14,607
<i>Do you have a 20</i>
<i>on gary navarro?</i>

934
00:42:14,607 --> 00:42:16,508
Yeah, he just
walked by.

935
00:42:16,508 --> 00:42:17,474
Why?

936
00:42:17,474 --> 00:42:18,474
<i>Get him!</i>

937
00:42:18,474 --> 00:42:20,374
Hey! Stop!

938
00:42:20,374 --> 00:42:21,474
Go. I'll check on ryland.

939
00:42:23,807 --> 00:42:24,907
He's seizing.

940
00:42:24,907 --> 00:42:26,374
He's bradying down.

941
00:42:26,374 --> 00:42:27,907
I need a crash cart
and ativan.

942
00:42:27,907 --> 00:42:29,207
Find dr. Danoff.

943
00:42:29,207 --> 00:42:30,640
Now!

944
00:42:38,174 --> 00:42:40,241
Stay right there, gary.

945
00:42:46,107 --> 00:42:47,241
Isabelle.

946
00:42:47,241 --> 00:42:48,508
Isabelle!

947
00:42:48,508 --> 00:42:50,141
Oh, god.

948
00:42:50,141 --> 00:42:51,940
Somebody call an ambulance!

949
00:42:53,141 --> 00:42:54,807
What's everybody
standing around for?

950
00:42:54,807 --> 00:42:56,607
Somebody call an ambulance!

951
00:42:56,607 --> 00:42:59,640
They're on
their way!

952
00:43:02,474 --> 00:43:04,341
Somebody call an ambulance...
dad...

953
00:43:19,774 --> 00:43:21,774
what am i?

954
00:43:23,874 --> 00:43:25,241
[Daniel]:
<i>It's miraculous, shawn.</i>

955
00:43:27,174 --> 00:43:29,307
I watch you
heal someone, and...

956
00:43:29,307 --> 00:43:32,441
it makes me wonder
why they hate us so much.

957
00:43:32,441 --> 00:43:33,807
They hate us

958
00:43:33,807 --> 00:43:35,707
because you're
killing them, daniel.

959
00:43:35,707 --> 00:43:38,807
They're afraid of us.
I can't blame them.

960
00:43:38,807 --> 00:43:40,540
You make it sound

961
00:43:40,540 --> 00:43:44,441
like we acted out of
some sort of blood lust.

962
00:43:44,441 --> 00:43:47,774
These were precise,
tactical strikes, shawn,

963
00:43:47,774 --> 00:43:49,707
and you
and every other 4400

964
00:43:49,707 --> 00:43:51,774
are ultimately much safer
because of them.

965
00:43:51,774 --> 00:43:53,207
You killed people.

966
00:43:53,207 --> 00:43:55,274
That's not what we discussed
when you approached me.

967
00:43:55,274 --> 00:43:56,640
I gave you money

968
00:43:56,640 --> 00:43:57,974
to start a defensive arm
for the center

969
00:43:57,974 --> 00:43:59,640
in case the government
ever came after us again.

970
00:43:59,640 --> 00:44:00,774
It was a precaution.

971
00:44:00,774 --> 00:44:02,408
And all we've done

972
00:44:02,408 --> 00:44:03,774
is taken
precautionary measures.

973
00:44:03,774 --> 00:44:04,874
Shawn, do you think
that because

974
00:44:04,874 --> 00:44:06,174
their inhibitor program
was exposed

975
00:44:06,174 --> 00:44:08,607
that the government's
just going to leave us in peace?

976
00:44:08,607 --> 00:44:10,974
No, they know
we've gotten stronger,

977
00:44:10,974 --> 00:44:12,607
which threatens
their hold on power,

978
00:44:12,607 --> 00:44:14,307
which increases their need
to eliminate us.

979
00:44:14,307 --> 00:44:17,007
So we strike first?

980
00:44:17,007 --> 00:44:19,474
Is that it?

981
00:44:19,474 --> 00:44:21,807
Is that what happens
on the 19th?

982
00:44:21,807 --> 00:44:23,707
Look, shawn,

983
00:44:23,707 --> 00:44:26,640
you do great work
at that center of yours.

984
00:44:26,640 --> 00:44:28,974
You just focus on that.

985
00:44:28,974 --> 00:44:30,107
I don't want to distract you.

986
00:44:30,107 --> 00:44:31,474
Knowledge can be a burden.

987
00:44:33,940 --> 00:44:36,573
And thanks
for helping t.j. Out.

988
00:44:36,573 --> 00:44:39,141
You're a hero
to your own people.

989
00:44:39,141 --> 00:44:41,840
Never forget that.

990
00:44:44,508 --> 00:44:45,840
Yeah.

991
00:44:49,207 --> 00:44:50,408
It did not work,
you know.

992
00:44:50,408 --> 00:44:51,707
Ryland was o.d.'ing,

993
00:44:51,707 --> 00:44:53,607
but the doctors
pulled him out of it.

994
00:44:53,607 --> 00:44:56,540
He'll be awake
within a couple of hours.

995
00:44:56,540 --> 00:44:58,573
Well, i'm sure
you're as disappointed as i am.

996
00:44:59,673 --> 00:45:00,807
Don't worry.

997
00:45:00,807 --> 00:45:01,807
We'll get him.

998
00:45:01,807 --> 00:45:03,940
Let's talk about
wesley hauser.

999
00:45:03,940 --> 00:45:06,640
You first met him
in quarantine.

1000
00:45:06,640 --> 00:45:07,907
I liked wes.

1001
00:45:07,907 --> 00:45:10,074
He was 10 kinds of crazy,

1002
00:45:10,074 --> 00:45:11,774
but his heart was
in the right place.

1003
00:45:11,774 --> 00:45:13,274
I guess he was bipolar
or something,

1004
00:45:13,274 --> 00:45:14,874
but he never
took medication.

1005
00:45:14,874 --> 00:45:17,041
After quarantine,
he lived on the streets.

1006
00:45:17,041 --> 00:45:19,573
I used to visit him
down at the docks.

1007
00:45:19,573 --> 00:45:21,607
You know, give him food,
a little money.

1008
00:45:21,607 --> 00:45:22,974
So when did you decide
to kill him?

1009
00:45:24,207 --> 00:45:26,274
Wes, he didn't need my help
with that.

1010
00:45:26,274 --> 00:45:29,408
He drank about
three bottles of mad dog a day.

1011
00:45:29,408 --> 00:45:34,940
One morning about a month ago,
i went down to see him, and...

1012
00:45:34,940 --> 00:45:37,508
i found him by the dumpster.

1013
00:45:37,508 --> 00:45:38,640
Dead.

1014
00:45:38,640 --> 00:45:40,141
And somewhere

1015
00:45:40,141 --> 00:45:41,508
in the middle
of your grieving process,

1016
00:45:41,508 --> 00:45:42,540
you figured he'd make
a handy decoy.

1017
00:45:42,540 --> 00:45:45,441
Hauser wouldn't
have minded.

1018
00:45:45,441 --> 00:45:47,374
Going back
to his marine corps days.

1019
00:45:47,374 --> 00:45:48,774
So when i found him,

1020
00:45:48,774 --> 00:45:51,673
i said a word or two
over his body,

1021
00:45:51,673 --> 00:45:54,974
and i pushed him
into elliott bay.

1022
00:45:54,974 --> 00:45:56,740
So how long have you been
working with this nova group?

1023
00:45:56,740 --> 00:45:58,207
Did someone approach you,

1024
00:45:58,207 --> 00:45:59,508
or was the whole thing
your idea?

1025
00:45:59,508 --> 00:46:01,740
Tell me...

1026
00:46:01,740 --> 00:46:03,174
you and this girlfriend
of yours...

1027
00:46:03,174 --> 00:46:06,174
is it like a role-playing thing
you get up to?

1028
00:46:06,174 --> 00:46:08,074
Or is she actually
taking you into these...

1029
00:46:08,074 --> 00:46:09,807
i don't know.
What do you call it?

1030
00:46:09,807 --> 00:46:11,508
Fantasy worlds?

1031
00:46:12,840 --> 00:46:14,907
Oh, and this guy marco...

1032
00:46:14,907 --> 00:46:17,241
does he know

1033
00:46:17,241 --> 00:46:19,508
that you're too...

1034
00:46:19,508 --> 00:46:20,874
embarrassed
to tell your partner

1035
00:46:20,874 --> 00:46:23,740
that you two have been dating?

1036
00:46:23,740 --> 00:46:25,673
Done showing off?

1037
00:46:25,673 --> 00:46:27,074
Why don't you tell us

1038
00:46:27,074 --> 00:46:29,408
